gnunet.org bibliography is a mixture of various documents.

The TODO (and work-in-progress) here is a re-implementation of
freehaven's anonbib[0], preferable in a language that requires
no big bootstrap (or even itself to build itself),
so the obvious pick could be a lisp.
Another candidate could be Skribilo[1][2] combined with other
existing tools.

More TODO:
Gather sourcecode of our own publications, so that they can be generated
and no PDF has to be used (for those where this can be applied).

0: https://www.freehaven.net/anonbib/
1: http://www.nongnu.org/skribilo/doc/user-7.html#biblio
2: http://www.nongnu.org/skribilo/